HomebrewFrom sourceMCP drop-in <pre><code>brew install aquifer-labs/tap/artesian
</code></pre> <pre><code>cargo install --git https://github.com/aquifer-labs/artesian artesian-cli
artesian init --backend sqlite-vec   # zero infrastructure
</code></pre> <p>Add to <code>claude_desktop_config.json</code> or your MCP settings:</p> <pre><code>{
  "artesian-memory": {
    "command": "artesian-mcp",
    "args": ["--config", "artesian.toml"]
  }
}
</code></pre> <p><code>artesian init</code> writes the config. Works with Claude Code, Codex, opencode, and any MCP client.</p> 10,144 → 1,260 tokens Token savings — measured on every recall.     Artesian records baseline vs returned tokens on every <code>loop.recall</code> and     <code>memory.context</code> call. The example above is a single session; your live     total updates in real time.     Run <code>artesian tokens</code> to see your own numbers, or query     <code>memory.savings</code> from MCP.     Full details →
